WEBVTT

00:02.561 --> 00:04.561
[bells jingling]

00:04.563 --> 00:05.987
[belches]

00:06.065 --> 00:07.397
♪

00:07.399 --> 00:08.656
D'oh!

00:08.734 --> 00:10.917
[barking]

00:10.994 --> 00:12.219
[grunts]

00:16.500 --> 00:18.434
♪

00:23.265 --> 00:24.765
♪

00:24.841 --> 00:27.918
♪<i> Bowl me to the moon</i> ♪

00:27.920 --> 00:31.846
♪<i> And roll me to the stars</i> ♪

00:31.924 --> 00:33.106
♪<i> Hey</i> ♪

00:33.183 --> 00:35.850
♪<i> This is more</i>
<i> than just a game</i> ♪

00:35.928 --> 00:39.687
♪<i> For big fat dopes in bars</i> ♪

00:39.765 --> 00:40.688
♪<i> No</i> ♪

00:40.766 --> 00:42.949
♪<i> For lazy guys</i> ♪

00:43.026 --> 00:45.360
♪<i> This is a sport</i> ♪

00:45.437 --> 00:48.005
♪<i> Doo bap,</i>
<i> doo boop bee boo wow</i> ♪

00:50.793 --> 00:51.717
[pins clatter]

00:51.794 --> 00:53.110
It's today.

00:53.112 --> 00:54.202
It's today!

00:54.280 --> 00:56.371
-What day is it?
-Saturday.

00:56.448 --> 00:57.598
It's today!

00:58.708 --> 01:01.226
[exclaims weakly]

01:03.564 --> 01:05.230
[swallows]
Whoopie.

01:05.307 --> 01:07.624
Move over Los Angeles
and Philadelphia.

01:07.626 --> 01:11.311
It's Springfield's turn
to have its drunken sports fans

01:11.463 --> 01:14.631
climb streetlights
and burn down the town.

01:14.633 --> 01:17.467
That's right, finally,
after years of phantom fouls

01:17.469 --> 01:18.819
and butt fumbles,

01:18.971 --> 01:22.730
one of our beloved local
sports teams, the "Pin Pals,"

01:22.732 --> 01:24.658
have made it
to the state championship.

01:24.734 --> 01:27.920
With Springfield's years
of failure at sports, the arts,

01:27.996 --> 01:30.497
and our disastrous toddler
boxing tournament,

01:30.574 --> 01:34.426
it's no exaggeration to say
that our "Super Bowlers" are

01:34.503 --> 01:38.380
garnering tremendous
pin-terest. [chuckling]

01:38.456 --> 01:39.489
♪

01:39.491 --> 01:40.432
♪<i> Yeah!</i> ♪

01:43.086 --> 01:44.161
♪<i> Yeah!</i> ♪

01:44.163 --> 01:46.847
Finally, strikes I can support.

01:46.923 --> 01:47.848
[cheering]

01:47.924 --> 01:49.757
Mayor, you've been
accused of being

01:49.835 --> 01:51.852
a fair-weather fan
for this team.

01:51.928 --> 01:53.019
Not true.

01:53.096 --> 01:55.763
I am a dyed-in-the-wool
fan of these...

01:55.841 --> 01:56.857
[quietly]
Bowlers.

01:56.859 --> 01:58.766
Bowlers?! Really?

01:58.786 --> 02:00.360
People still do that?

02:00.437 --> 02:03.530
So you don't mind that they say
you're jumping on the bandwagon?

02:03.607 --> 02:07.459
Let me just say, no one jumps
later or harder than I.

02:07.536 --> 02:11.130
To the Pin Heads,
eh... Pin Pals.

02:12.282 --> 02:14.249
[playing
"For He's a Jolly Good Fellow"]

02:15.469 --> 02:20.380
[announcer]<i> And now,</i>
<i> your heroes, the Pin Pals.</i>

02:20.382 --> 02:21.306
[cheering]

02:21.383 --> 02:23.475
[chuckles]
How you doing?

02:23.552 --> 02:24.885
Marry me!

02:24.961 --> 02:26.386
Oh, yeah. Sure, sure.

02:26.463 --> 02:28.630
Anyhoo, I could never
have made it

02:28.649 --> 02:32.634
without my very good friends,
Homer, Carl, Flanders,

02:32.711 --> 02:36.638
and that new guy from Portugal
whose, uh, name I forget.

02:36.715 --> 02:38.615
[speaking Portuguese]

02:43.497 --> 02:45.389
Yi-yo-yu!

02:45.391 --> 02:46.723
[cheering]

02:46.725 --> 02:48.725
He don't speak
the good English or nothing,

02:48.727 --> 02:50.727
but he sure as hell
can roll strikes.

02:50.729 --> 02:54.731
And he's got a very hot sister,
or girlfriend, or mother...

02:54.733 --> 02:56.258
It's really hard to tell.

02:58.662 --> 02:59.994
<i> Eu te amo.</i>

03:00.072 --> 03:01.421
All right.
Based on my experience,

03:01.498 --> 03:02.923
that is<i> not</i> his mother.

03:02.999 --> 03:06.668
Uh, I just want to say, we
aren't just doing this for us.

03:06.745 --> 03:10.597
It is going to mean the world
to this entire town.

03:10.674 --> 03:12.340
Excuse me, but I don't see

03:12.359 --> 03:14.935
how the town possibly
benefits from this.

03:15.011 --> 03:16.195
We'd be helped a lot more

03:16.346 --> 03:18.605
by a traffic light
on Elm Street.

03:18.682 --> 03:20.090
[booing]

03:20.092 --> 03:23.017
Smack him with his bone!
Smack him good!

03:23.095 --> 03:25.019
Uh, my friends and neighbors--

03:25.097 --> 03:26.371
Reluctant neighbors.

03:26.448 --> 03:30.709
[stammers] I'd just like us
to, uh, bow our heads,

03:30.786 --> 03:32.452
-and thank--
-Stupid Flanders.

03:32.529 --> 03:34.438
Turns everything good
into church.

03:34.440 --> 03:36.957
Just once,
can you not mention God?

03:37.033 --> 03:39.776
All righty, then,
let me just s-say way to go,

03:39.778 --> 03:41.386
Big Guy in the Sky.

03:41.463 --> 03:44.965
[both]
And his son, Jesus Christ. Amen.

03:45.041 --> 03:47.041
Jesus is God's rod.

03:47.119 --> 03:50.287
[mocking laugh]
Jesus is God's rod.

03:50.289 --> 03:51.788
[chuckles] Blasphemy.

03:52.791 --> 03:57.477
And now, O captain,
my captain, Homer Simpson.

03:57.554 --> 03:59.296
[whooping]

03:59.298 --> 04:01.907
There's one word
that defines this team.

04:01.984 --> 04:04.726
And that word isn't "can"
or "might."

04:04.728 --> 04:08.655
That word is, uh, wait a minute.

04:08.732 --> 04:10.490
Cards out of order...

04:10.567 --> 04:12.567
Can't read my own writing here.

04:12.569 --> 04:14.828
Oh, okay, it's "will."

04:14.980 --> 04:17.214
Yes, we will!

04:18.908 --> 04:20.926
[chanting]
Let's go Pin Pals.

04:21.003 --> 04:22.928
Win that title.

04:23.005 --> 04:25.489
Win that title!

04:25.491 --> 04:30.060
-Let's get pickles.
-Let's get pickles.

04:31.013 --> 04:32.253
All right folks, break it up.

04:32.331 --> 04:34.439
Unless you're jerkin'
a gherkin, go on home.

04:37.519 --> 04:38.835
[happy groaning]

04:38.837 --> 04:42.172
Oh, Homie.
Today was magnificent.

04:42.190 --> 04:44.432
I always thought
bowling was just an excuse

04:44.510 --> 04:47.677
to get away from the kids
and drink a lot of beer.

04:47.679 --> 04:50.455
What? No. Never. What?

04:50.532 --> 04:53.683
But now it's made
the whole town proud of you.

04:53.685 --> 04:55.777
And I'm part of the town,

04:55.854 --> 04:57.445
so this comes from the heart.

04:57.523 --> 05:00.206
Ugh, I can't say it.
I don't want to say it.

05:00.283 --> 05:02.192
You can't make me say it,
and I won't say it.

05:02.194 --> 05:03.693
Or even think it!

05:03.695 --> 05:05.095
Aw, thank you, son.

05:06.140 --> 05:08.289
I love you all. Water my plants.

05:08.367 --> 05:10.124
You don't have any plants.

05:10.202 --> 05:12.060
Then we're good. Bye.

05:17.543 --> 05:19.026
♪

05:25.734 --> 05:27.217
Ain't this the life?

05:27.219 --> 05:28.568
Whirly birding,

05:28.570 --> 05:31.221
full can of soda,
two bags of peanuts.

05:31.223 --> 05:32.722
I've never known such luxury.

05:32.724 --> 05:34.891
I could die right now
a happy man.

05:34.910 --> 05:36.835
[Barney]
This is your captain speaking.

05:36.912 --> 05:39.062
Please buckle up
as we attempt to clear

05:39.064 --> 05:40.672
the treacherous mountain peak.

05:40.749 --> 05:41.831
Wha--?!

05:43.159 --> 05:46.595
No worries. Every chopper
in town takes this route.

05:51.167 --> 05:52.926
[alarm buzzing]

05:53.854 --> 05:57.097
Overweight?
How is that possible?

05:57.173 --> 06:01.101
Pilot, five passengers,
five 14-pound balls...

06:01.177 --> 06:03.028
Uh, I wanted
a little extra oomph,

06:03.179 --> 06:05.772
so I actually brought
a 16-pound ball.

06:05.849 --> 06:09.701
Me, too. By which I mean
I brought two 16-pound balls.

06:09.778 --> 06:12.112
Anyone else want to brag
about their balls?

06:12.188 --> 06:13.538
I mean, seriously?

06:13.615 --> 06:16.524
Fausto bring this.
For good luck.

06:16.526 --> 06:18.710
Yi-yo-yu!

06:20.772 --> 06:23.215
I'm gonna have to put her
down on the mountain.

06:23.291 --> 06:25.509
Of all the times to be sober.

06:27.129 --> 06:28.720
[both whimpering]

06:28.797 --> 06:31.014
This could be it.

06:32.951 --> 06:34.726
At least I can say goodbye.

06:34.803 --> 06:36.620
-[Marge]<i> Hello?</i>
-Marge...

06:36.622 --> 06:39.789
<i> We're not home now,</i>
<i> so please don't rob us.</i>

06:39.791 --> 06:41.048
<i> Leave a message.</i>

06:41.126 --> 06:44.127
[pants] Listen, Marge,
we've had our arguments,

06:44.146 --> 06:46.813
we've had our things,
but thank God I have the time

06:46.890 --> 06:48.556
to tell you how I really feel...

06:48.634 --> 06:50.725
-[automated voice]<i> Mailbox full.</i>
-D'oh!

06:50.802 --> 06:52.661
[alarm continues buzzing]

06:54.306 --> 06:56.164
-[alarm wailing]
-[all exclaiming]

07:01.755 --> 07:03.088
Whee! Ah!

07:08.320 --> 07:11.245
As your captain,
one thing is clear:

07:11.323 --> 07:12.989
we must get off this mountain.

07:12.991 --> 07:14.658
And I'm no expert on mountains,

07:14.660 --> 07:17.269
but I say down is this way.

07:19.665 --> 07:21.022
D'oh!

07:24.352 --> 07:25.569
D'oh!

07:29.283 --> 07:30.765
-What the...?
-[satellite beeping]

07:30.842 --> 07:32.284
[Carl]
I wouldn't leave
just yet, Homer.

07:32.360 --> 07:34.786
Our new friend there
still hasn't woken up.

07:34.938 --> 07:37.271
Oh, God!
Spanish-what's-his-name.

07:37.349 --> 07:40.208
It's Portuguese-what's-his-name,
you idiot.

07:40.794 --> 07:41.868
[Marge]
<i> Chief?</i>

07:41.945 --> 07:44.187
-Is there any word?
-'Fraid not.

07:44.189 --> 07:46.873
Apparently they knocked out
a cell phone tower

07:46.950 --> 07:48.115
on the way down.

07:48.193 --> 07:51.027
Wait, wait!
Uh, now we're getting somewhere.

07:51.029 --> 07:52.304
Yeah.

07:53.289 --> 07:56.216
Oh, thank God, man.
I was starting to lose all hope.

07:56.292 --> 07:58.051
[Italian accent]
Oh, you hungry cops

07:58.127 --> 07:59.703
put-a my kids through college.

07:59.705 --> 08:02.814
Seven-a sisters.
Not the women's colleges.

08:02.891 --> 08:04.483
I have-a seven daughters:

08:04.559 --> 08:07.635
Gia, Mia, Pia, Tia, Zia,

08:07.713 --> 08:10.396
Iphigenia, and then Emily,
for some reason.

08:10.473 --> 08:11.531
I don't know.

08:13.068 --> 08:15.476
Hmm, still barely breathing.

08:15.554 --> 08:18.163
[sighs] If the Lord could
carry His cross,

08:18.165 --> 08:20.390
I can carry this poor soul.

08:20.392 --> 08:22.392
[Homer]
<i> Huh? Well, look at that.</i>

08:22.394 --> 08:26.004
<i> Flanders risking his own life</i>
<i> to save another.</i>

08:26.081 --> 08:27.080
<i> Wow.</i>

08:27.156 --> 08:29.415
Homer, could you get
my water bottle?

08:29.492 --> 08:30.967
No.

08:34.589 --> 08:35.997
-[phone ringing]
-A phone!

08:36.074 --> 08:37.182
Someone's got cell service.

08:37.333 --> 08:38.925
Hello, Moe speaking.

08:39.002 --> 08:40.927
Hi, I'm looking
for a Mr. Simpson.

08:41.004 --> 08:42.412
First name, Homer.

08:42.414 --> 08:44.080
Oh, I recognize that voice.

08:44.082 --> 08:45.598
You ever call me again.
you little puke,

08:45.675 --> 08:49.194
I'm gonna cut you up, use your
intestines as violin strings,

08:49.271 --> 08:50.937
and play
"Flight of the Bumblebee!"

08:51.089 --> 08:53.681
I'm gonna go
Rimsky-Korsakov on yas.

08:53.759 --> 08:56.017
I'm just trying to find my dad.

08:56.094 --> 08:58.278
Yeah, right.
Try looking in hell, hell boy!

08:58.354 --> 09:00.096
[Bart over phone]
<i> Ay caramba!</i>

09:00.098 --> 09:01.614
Moe, you idiot!

09:01.691 --> 09:04.042
You were the only one
with cellular service.

09:04.119 --> 09:07.361
[exclaims] What have I done?
Me and my anger issues.

09:07.439 --> 09:10.456
Dr. Rubenstein's gonna be
so disappointed.

09:10.533 --> 09:12.092
[grunts]

09:13.036 --> 09:14.702
[muttering]
Stupid avalanche.

09:14.780 --> 09:17.055
[line ringing, beeps]

09:17.132 --> 09:18.056
[phone beeps]

09:18.133 --> 09:20.141
[clicking]

09:20.969 --> 09:22.786
No connection.

09:22.788 --> 09:24.287
And it's almost night.

09:24.289 --> 09:27.290
[sobs]
I feel so much regret.

09:27.292 --> 09:31.144
I never got the chance
to tell my son I loved him.

09:31.220 --> 09:34.055
Never? You're 87 years old.

09:34.132 --> 09:36.466
Uh, it was on my "to do" list.

09:36.468 --> 09:37.483
Take a look.

09:37.560 --> 09:38.493
See?

09:42.974 --> 09:45.825
Still no sign
of the missing bowlers.

09:45.902 --> 09:47.327
And one thing I must say now,

09:47.403 --> 09:49.570
there is nothing
a newscaster loves better

09:49.648 --> 09:50.997
than missing people,

09:50.999 --> 09:52.924
be they on a mountain,
in a submarine,

09:53.001 --> 09:55.242
or, preferably,
deep under rubble.

09:55.262 --> 09:56.836
Even if we know they're dead,

09:56.913 --> 09:58.913
we'll keep it quiet
for a few days,

09:58.990 --> 10:00.657
just to keep the ratings up.

10:00.659 --> 10:03.918
And now, tonight's lotto,
which no one ever wins.

10:03.995 --> 10:05.562
[chuckling]

10:06.498 --> 10:07.588
No...!

10:07.666 --> 10:10.516
[voice fading]
Why am I talking like this?

10:10.593 --> 10:14.020
I'm not falling,
just clinging to the edge!

10:15.006 --> 10:18.617
Oh, man, that was close.
How deep is that thing, anyway?

10:18.693 --> 10:21.620
Only one way to find out.

10:24.532 --> 10:26.215
[ball clatters
through bowling pins]

10:26.217 --> 10:29.519
Gentlemen, I fear
we're starting to hallucinate.

10:29.521 --> 10:30.962
That's crazy talk.

10:31.039 --> 10:33.131
Barney, pick up the spare.

10:35.785 --> 10:36.968
[pin clunks]

10:38.472 --> 10:41.622
Listen to me. Time to get your
cuckoos back in your clocks.

10:41.700 --> 10:44.033
We're approaching
the point of no return.

10:44.035 --> 10:46.419
Flanders, h-how do I put this?

10:46.496 --> 10:48.129
I was thinking
I might want to...

10:48.206 --> 10:50.315
oh, this is so embarrassing...

10:50.433 --> 10:51.391
pray.

10:51.467 --> 10:55.136
There are no atheists
in foxholes.

10:55.213 --> 10:57.213
Oh, yes.
Foxes are very religious.

10:57.215 --> 10:59.883
I'd be praying if a bunch
of guys in red vests on horses

10:59.885 --> 11:01.234
were trying to kill me.

11:01.310 --> 11:03.386
Now, make with the Our Father.

11:03.388 --> 11:05.497
♪

11:05.573 --> 11:08.224
[bowling announcer]
<i> Still no word</i>
<i> on the Springfield team.</i>

11:08.226 --> 11:12.253
<i> Please observe an anticipatory</i>
<i> 60-second moment of silence.</i>

11:14.065 --> 11:15.507
[ball rolling]

11:15.583 --> 11:17.008
[bowler]
Wasn't me.

11:18.494 --> 11:19.594
Strike.

11:21.256 --> 11:24.349
My friends, if we just
have faith in the good Lord

11:24.426 --> 11:26.518
who blew us to bits
on the side of the mountain,

11:26.594 --> 11:27.686
we'll be okay.

11:27.762 --> 11:30.838
Hey, Churchy Joe,
tell that to my piggies!

11:30.916 --> 11:32.524
The word "frostbite"
sounds so cutesy

11:32.600 --> 11:35.084
when people get it
at Buffalo Bills games,

11:35.086 --> 11:37.344
but when it happens to you, ugh!

11:37.422 --> 11:40.924
Well, I think things
will be just fine.

11:40.926 --> 11:43.776
Really? And who made you
Optimist Prime?

11:43.853 --> 11:47.113
I broke open my first aid kit.

11:47.190 --> 11:50.024
-[gasping]
-Anybody else holding out
on anything?

11:50.101 --> 11:51.692
Like me with these
two bags of peanuts,

11:51.770 --> 11:55.755
which I'm going to eat right
now despite my peanut allergy.

11:57.200 --> 11:58.717
[muffled grunt]

12:00.369 --> 12:03.221
See this? This is the face
of a survivor.

12:03.372 --> 12:04.797
[chuckles]

12:04.874 --> 12:07.467
Uh, Christmas decorations?

12:07.543 --> 12:09.543
Uh, in October?

12:09.621 --> 12:12.397
We've done everything we can
to help your father, so...

12:12.474 --> 12:15.124
I thought this would
help us feel better.

12:15.126 --> 12:17.810
[sobbing]

12:17.963 --> 12:20.721
Bart, they say a kid
is only as happy

12:20.799 --> 12:22.723
as their saddest parent.

12:22.801 --> 12:25.034
♪

12:28.397 --> 12:30.564
Zoom in on
the heartbroken family.

12:30.584 --> 12:31.916
Zoom, I say!

12:31.918 --> 12:33.418
No. I can't.

12:33.495 --> 12:35.828
I didn't go to journalism
school to be a ghoul.

12:35.905 --> 12:37.922
I went because
it was an easy major.

12:37.999 --> 12:41.818
Take your soul and get the hell
out of local news.

12:41.820 --> 12:42.986
[wind howling]

12:42.988 --> 12:45.387
Fausto... not good.

12:45.389 --> 12:47.490
My friend, we will get you back

12:47.492 --> 12:50.751
and then you and I will have
a grand old time.

12:50.829 --> 12:52.586
I hear you silently agreeing.

12:52.664 --> 12:55.348
-[groans weakly]
-We'll go fishing
and make s'mores

12:55.424 --> 12:57.333
and we'll be best friends.

12:57.335 --> 12:58.943
You're a Catholic
and I'm a Christian,

12:59.020 --> 13:00.686
but we'll work through that.

13:00.763 --> 13:02.947
Ooh, more silent agreement.

13:03.024 --> 13:04.524
Here, my friend, let me...
let me set you down

13:04.600 --> 13:06.659
so we can talk about
our great future.

13:07.862 --> 13:10.530
Save your breath, pal.
He's dead.

13:10.682 --> 13:13.366
No! No, he's not dead.
H-He's just resting.

13:13.442 --> 13:15.685
Oh, Lord,
you can't be this cruel.

13:15.687 --> 13:18.855
Sorry, man. I knew
he was a goner a while ago,

13:18.857 --> 13:21.040
but I liked
watching you carry him.

13:21.117 --> 13:22.692
We were gonna make s'mores.

13:22.694 --> 13:25.378
Now there'll just be s'nothing.
[sniffles]

13:25.454 --> 13:27.955
Poor Fausto. Poor Flanders.

13:28.033 --> 13:29.790
You really tried, man.

13:29.868 --> 13:31.367
Oh, I mean it.

13:31.369 --> 13:33.219
I'm not just hugging you
because you're warm,

13:33.296 --> 13:35.054
although that's
a big part of it.

13:35.131 --> 13:36.314
You're a good man.

13:36.391 --> 13:38.316
Homer, I knew you had a heart.

13:38.393 --> 13:40.634
Just like the Cowardly Lion.

13:40.712 --> 13:44.155
He always had a heart.
What he lacked was courage.

13:44.232 --> 13:46.807
And the Scarecrow
lacked straw, right?

13:46.885 --> 13:48.384
No, he was nothing but straw.

13:48.386 --> 13:51.979
Wow. I'm looking at everything
with new eyes.

13:51.981 --> 13:53.890
Just like the Tin Man.

13:53.892 --> 13:55.908
That's not what the Tin Man...

13:55.985 --> 13:57.410
Look, just give me another hug.

13:58.413 --> 14:01.822
All right, gentlemen, there's
a subject we need to discuss.

14:01.900 --> 14:04.992
Now we've waited long enough,
I'm just going to say it:

14:05.070 --> 14:07.512
It is time that we resorted
to cannibalism.

14:07.589 --> 14:08.680
Mmm.

14:08.756 --> 14:10.923
What? No. Absolutely not.

14:11.076 --> 14:12.592
I'm not saying we eat him.

14:12.668 --> 14:15.219
I'm saying we prepare him
to be eaten.

14:15.296 --> 14:17.838
If he gets frozen, we'll just
end up with junk food,

14:17.858 --> 14:19.749
like his hair or his toenails.

14:19.751 --> 14:20.750
What?

14:20.752 --> 14:22.026
Stop! Stop! Stop!

14:22.863 --> 14:24.437
Bawk! Bawk! Bawk!

14:24.513 --> 14:27.031
Just gimme a wing. Come on.
You got two, come on!

14:27.108 --> 14:29.284
No eating people.

14:31.687 --> 14:33.496
♪

14:35.375 --> 14:38.025
[Flanders]
<i> If I eat these,</i>
<i> and don't share them...</i>

14:38.103 --> 14:39.785
<i> it breaks every value I have.</i>

14:39.862 --> 14:43.439
<i> But just thinking about it</i>
<i> also means I've sinned. Hmm.</i>

14:43.441 --> 14:45.441
<i> I must say, it's a lot easier</i>
<i> to have this debate</i>

14:45.443 --> 14:47.218
<i> with my mouth full of matzah.</i>

14:47.295 --> 14:49.053
-Flanders?
-[gulps]

14:49.130 --> 14:51.372
-Yes?
-It's so clear to me now.

14:51.449 --> 14:53.057
You're the better man, Ned.

14:53.134 --> 14:54.300
Well, that's not true.

14:54.302 --> 14:56.177
You've got the highest average
on the team.

14:56.212 --> 14:57.562
I'm nothing compared to you.

14:57.639 --> 14:59.972
Have you noticed I haven't
called you "stupid Flanders"

15:00.049 --> 15:01.382
once on this mountain?

15:01.459 --> 15:03.884
What do you want,
a Nobel Peace Prize?

15:03.962 --> 15:06.887
Sorry, sorry,
I really do appreciate it.

15:06.965 --> 15:08.222
It's just that
I've come to realize

15:08.299 --> 15:10.466
I'm not a natural leader,
like you.

15:10.468 --> 15:13.244
The Lord has a time and a place
for everyone, my friend.

15:13.321 --> 15:14.971
Homer, if the high altitude

15:14.973 --> 15:16.489
hasn't turned
your brain to mulch,

15:16.565 --> 15:18.399
would you like
to lead us in prayer?

15:18.476 --> 15:21.252
Heavenly father,
who art in truck stop.

15:21.329 --> 15:24.422
Ping-pong. Rock.
Zipper. Jambalaya.

15:24.499 --> 15:25.831
[moans]

15:25.908 --> 15:27.817
-[coughing]
-Now, don't worry.

15:27.819 --> 15:30.153
Just 'cause one of us
has a tickle in his whistle

15:30.155 --> 15:31.930
doesn't mean... [coughs]

15:32.006 --> 15:34.182
[coughing, wheezing]

15:36.102 --> 15:39.345
We're in the tenth frame,
people.

15:39.422 --> 15:42.589
If you want me to eat youse
later, just say nothing.

15:42.667 --> 15:44.609
[moans weakly]

15:44.760 --> 15:46.694
♪

15:54.621 --> 15:56.512
-♪
-[snoring]

15:56.514 --> 15:58.272
Chief, any news?

15:58.349 --> 16:00.016
About what? Oh, right.

16:00.018 --> 16:02.109
Um, Marge, with conditions

16:02.128 --> 16:04.445
as bad as they are
on that mountain,

16:04.522 --> 16:08.207
even if they somehow
did survive the crash, uh,

16:08.284 --> 16:10.376
oh, how can I put this gently?

16:10.453 --> 16:12.119
What do you mean, "gently"?

16:12.197 --> 16:13.972
You basically told me
they're dead!

16:14.048 --> 16:16.641
Will you please
leave my family be?

16:16.718 --> 16:19.218
[sighs] Never easy being a cop.

16:19.220 --> 16:20.703
Then why did you become one?

16:20.705 --> 16:23.556
'Cause I look great in blue.
It goes with my eyes.

16:23.632 --> 16:25.057
Your eyes are black.

16:25.134 --> 16:27.059
Well, I've wasted my life.

16:27.136 --> 16:28.802
[grunting]

16:28.880 --> 16:30.396
Patty and Selma?

16:30.473 --> 16:32.824
Oh, this day
couldn't get any worse.

16:32.900 --> 16:35.142
Is what my dad would say
if he were alive.

16:35.220 --> 16:37.720
Marge, dear,
at a time like this,

16:37.722 --> 16:40.498
all we want to do
is sit and hold your hand.

16:40.575 --> 16:42.959
No talk. Just love.

16:44.062 --> 16:46.320
I did want to say one thing:

16:46.397 --> 16:48.339
"Better get your booty shorts
to the cleaners

16:48.416 --> 16:50.824
"because you're gonna be
the most popular widow

16:50.902 --> 16:52.735
on the pickleball circuit."

16:52.737 --> 16:54.178
He's not dead!

16:54.255 --> 16:56.088
Well, we can't be sure...

16:56.165 --> 16:58.499
But we did use generative AI

16:58.576 --> 17:01.001
to make an image of Homer
as a corpse.

17:01.079 --> 17:03.187
To get you used
to the idea, dear.

17:06.751 --> 17:09.027
Some of these we had
even before the crash.

17:09.103 --> 17:11.254
He's not dead. He's not dead!

17:11.256 --> 17:14.198
In fact, I bet he's
even going to save the day.

17:14.275 --> 17:17.260
-[suppressed laughter]
-Can you excuse us?

17:17.278 --> 17:19.704
We need to go outside and laugh.

17:19.781 --> 17:22.390
[wind howling]

17:22.466 --> 17:23.949
[Homer]
<i> Oh, is this it?</i>

17:24.026 --> 17:25.768
<i> My story ends now?</i>

17:25.770 --> 17:30.506
<i>Buried in the snow, frozen alone</i>
<i> like broccoli in my freezer?</i>

17:32.460 --> 17:36.279
My dear son,
are you ready to join me?

17:36.281 --> 17:39.223
I am, Mommy.
Take me to the good place.

17:39.300 --> 17:43.377
Um... That's not exactly
where I am.

17:43.454 --> 17:46.289
They are very hard
on former left-wing radicals

17:46.291 --> 17:47.473
in the afterlife.

17:47.550 --> 17:48.808
What are you saying?

17:48.884 --> 17:52.128
I'm in a place with
a lot of incredible people.

17:52.130 --> 17:55.406
Machiavelli, Che Guevara,

17:55.558 --> 17:57.558
Casanova.

17:57.635 --> 18:00.561
Casanova. Oh, Casanova.

18:00.638 --> 18:05.658
I thought dying in 1798 would
keep me from being MeToo'd.

18:05.734 --> 18:07.502
Um... Um...

18:10.164 --> 18:13.091
Mom? What are you making?

18:13.167 --> 18:16.243
All of your father's favorites.
For when he comes back.

18:16.321 --> 18:18.412
Pork chops, glazed ham,

18:18.489 --> 18:21.933
fried hooves, snout surprise.

18:22.009 --> 18:24.677
Oh, I can't be in the same room
with that smell.

18:24.829 --> 18:27.513
Yeah, it's pretty disgusting.

18:27.590 --> 18:29.732
♪

18:32.761 --> 18:34.094
[Homer]
<i> Hey, someone's cooking.</i>

18:34.172 --> 18:35.988
<i> Marge is cooking!</i>

18:36.858 --> 18:38.783
I can't die here.

18:38.860 --> 18:40.343
My family needs me.

18:40.345 --> 18:42.011
My story is still being written.

18:42.013 --> 18:45.939
And the next word
in it is<i> yeeargh!</i>

18:46.017 --> 18:47.500
[grunts]

18:49.020 --> 18:51.537
You're coming too, friends.

18:51.614 --> 18:53.297
♪

19:01.883 --> 19:04.700
Hidilly doodily, Saviorino!

19:04.702 --> 19:09.188
For once, Flanders, you owe me.

19:12.894 --> 19:15.895
[organ music playing]

19:15.897 --> 19:19.231
Homer Simpson.
Hmm, what can I say?

19:19.308 --> 19:22.827
He slept through Mass.
He'd floss with a Bible ribbon.

19:22.978 --> 19:26.813
I'm afraid he leaves behind
no good deed to remember him by.

19:26.833 --> 19:31.652
Just another fat pinball
slipping past God's flippers.

19:31.729 --> 19:34.730
Here's something
the church never heard of:

19:34.732 --> 19:37.416
A guy coming back from the dead!

19:37.493 --> 19:40.011
-[all gasp]
-God bless him.

19:40.087 --> 19:42.847
My bald, beautiful boy.

19:42.924 --> 19:44.498
No good deeds, Reverend?

19:44.517 --> 19:46.909
I've got a new end
for your eulogy:

19:46.911 --> 19:49.261
Thank God for Homer Simpson!

19:49.338 --> 19:52.690
That's my dad.
Suck it, other dads.

19:54.176 --> 19:56.752
You miss two birthdays
and a school play

19:56.754 --> 19:59.447
and suddenly you're the bad guy.

20:02.184 --> 20:04.035
I knew you'd make it back.

20:04.186 --> 20:07.688
I knew it. I knew it.

20:07.765 --> 20:11.024
You were wrong.
You were wrong!

20:11.102 --> 20:13.377
And you were wrong,
preacher man.

20:13.454 --> 20:15.213
Just premature.

20:15.289 --> 20:19.199
I knew he'd make it.
Since five seconds ago.

